Quote:   The post-election inquests have attributed the defeat of the nationalists to various causes, ... Coates' [205] unpopularity and the Brains Trust. [fn] Economists, including the civil servants, R.M. Campbell, W.B. Sutch, and Professor Horace Belshaw (of Auckland University College), who advised Coates. The name was derived from Roosevelt's `Brain Trust'.
